Namibia (AP) _ Namibia has become the 24th country to ratify the Ottawa Convention banning land mines. The ban on use. The International Campaign to Ban Landmines and its former leader Jody Williams won the Nobel Peace Prize in 1997 for their work in bringing world attention to the issue. (sapa/pr/djw)
-- South Africa is to join more than 100 countries in Canada this week to sign a treaty banning the use or possession of anti-personnel mines. South African Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo is expected to sign the treaty in Ottawa.
